<DOC><DOCNO> AP890624-0053 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-24-89 0725EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BBC-Strike     06-24 0085</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BBC-Strike,0087</SECOND><HEAD>BBC Workers Strike for Second Day</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Members of three unions staged a seven-hour striketoday against the British Broadcasting Corp., the second job walkoutagainst BBC in as many days.   Today's strike began without incident at 11 a.m., the NationalUnion of Journalists announced.   About 9,000 workers are represented by that group _ theBroadcasting Trades Alliance and the Association of Cinematographic,Television and Allied Technicians.   The unions want a 16 percent pay raise. Management has offered 9percent.</TEXT></DOC>